# Autonomous Agent Guide: Building ImageZue on Next.js 15 & Vercel

## Welcome to ImageZue Development

You're building **ImageZue** - an AI-powered Image Generation Tool that creates stunning visuals from text prompts and allows users to manage, organize, and refine their AI-generated artwork. It combines advanced AI models with intuitive gallery management, prompt engineering, and image editing capabilities. Think of it as a cross between Midjourney, Adobe Creative Cloud, and Pinterest.

This guide will walk you through implementing features systematically with a focus on quality and incremental development.

NEVER RUN 'bun run build'. It ruins my dev server. Just run bun check.

**Environment Configuration**: Your development variables are in `.env.local`

If you can't access a page with curl, check `middleware.ts` because we use Auth.js to protect most routes.

## 🎨 Core ImageZue Features

ImageZue focuses on providing the best AI image generation experience:

### 🖼️ Image Generation
- Text-to-image generation using multiple AI models (DALL-E, Midjourney, Stable Diffusion)
- Advanced prompt engineering with style presets and modifiers
- Batch generation with variations and iterations
- Real-time generation progress tracking

### 📱 Gallery Management
- Personal image collections and albums
- Advanced search and filtering by prompts, styles, models
- Favorites and rating system
- Sharing and collaboration features

### ✨ Image Enhancement
- AI-powered upscaling and enhancement
- Style transfer and artistic filters
- Background removal and replacement
- Image editing with AI assistance

### 🎯 Prompt Engineering
- Prompt templates and presets
- Prompt history and favorites
- Community prompt sharing
- AI-powered prompt optimization

