## Design and Styling

- Always try to use UI components from shadcn/ui. It is already installed, but not all components are added. You can run my custom bash wrapper `shadcn` like this: `shadcn add button card` which adds only the components that are not already present. For example, if @/components/ui/button.tsx already exists, then this command will actually run the correct shadcn command under the hood to add card and skip button.
- Always use Tailwind CSS for styling. It is already installed.
- Always use icons from lucide-react. It is already installed.
- Try to create clean, sleek, modern, and minimal design that is responsive on both mobile and desktop browsers.
- Follow the design patterns, conventions, and styling applied in the project to remain consistent.
- Always use rounded corners (2xl or 3xl).
- Prefer the 'outline' variant for most buttons.

